Use the **Navigation Panel** on the left to organize, browse, and switch between your workspace sections such as **Overview**, **Guides**, **References**, and **Settings **\(see Figure 1\).

The **Header Bar**, located at the top of the screen, allows you to view your published site, sync with GitHub or GitLab, and log out of your account \(see Figure 1\).

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Figure 1: Navigation panel and header bar

With the Navigation Panel and Header Bar, you can easily move between tasks, track your workspace's progress, and maintain your documentation with efficiency.

## **Left Navigation Panel**

The **Left Navigation Panel**, located on the left side of the dashboard, provides structured access to all key areas of your workspace. This vertical menu helps you quickly navigate between different modules.

***Tip: ***The currently active tab is highlighted in color for easy navigation.

## **Header Bar**

The **Header Bar** is a persistent bar that appears across all dashboard views. It provides quick access to workspace identification, synchronization, and account options.

**Workspace Name:**

- Appears at the top\-left corner \(for example, *workspace\_docu*\).
- Identifies your current workspace.

### **Global Header Controls**

**View Published Site:**

- Opens the live, published version of your documentation in a new **end\-user** tab.
- Allows you to instantly preview how your published content appears to end users or team members.
- Use this option to verify layout, formatting, and visibility of your latest updates.

**Sync from Github/Gitlab:**

- Opens the **Source Control** panel on the right side of the dashboard.
- Allows you to authenticate and connect your GitHub or GitLab repository to Docuwiz for automated file synchronization.
- You can manage repository details, access tokens, and connection settings from this panel. ***Learn more about Connecting and Syncing with Source Control ***

**Theme Toggle \(Light / Dark Mode\):**

- Switches between **light** and **dark** display themes for improved viewing comfort.
- The selected theme is applied across the entire Docuwiz workspace interface.

**User Profile \(Avatar Icon\):**

- Located in the **top\-right corner** of the Header Bar.
- Clicking the profile icon opens a panel displaying your username and email address, along with a **Log Out** option.
- Use the **Log Out** option to securely sign out of your current session.
